Allow a previously configured network to be associated with. If attemptConnect is true, an attempt to connect to the selected network is initiated. This may result in the asynchronous delivery of state change events. Note: Network communication may not use Wi-Fi even if Wi-Fi is connected; traffic may instead be sent through another network, such as cellular data, Bluetooth tethering, or Ethernet. For example, traffic will never use a Wi-Fi network that does not provide Internet access (e.g. a wireless printer), if another network that does offer Internet access (e.g. cellular data) is available. Applications that need to ensure that their network traffic uses Wi-Fi should use APIs such as Network.bindSocket(java.net.Socket), Network.openConnection(java.net.URL), or ConnectivityManager.bindProcessToNetwork to do so.
